The paper presents a method for minimizing proofs of unsatisfiability, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The method is applied to reduce the size of a graph, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper also discusses the comparison of their method with existing algorithms, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
